<!-- /Premium Blog -->
<h1>Forest Service says media needs photography permit in wilderness areas, alarming First Amendment advocates</h1>
<div class="clearfix"></div>
<!-- /headline -->

              <div id="article_container">
                  <div id="top_images"><div><span class="resimg  adv-photo-large" data-image="http://media.oregonlive.com/environment_impact/photo/15920343-mmmain.jpg" data-position="article-main" />Mount Hood</span></div><div class="Caption">
        
            First Amendment advocates are alarmed by a U.S. Forest Service policy requiring journalists to get a permit to shoot videos in federal wilderness areas including those on Mount Hood.
        
        
            
                <em>(The Oregonian/2013)</em></div></div>

                  




<div id="Byline">
	<div class="EmailPrint">
		<a class="PrintLink" href="http://blog.oregonlive.com/environment_impact/print.html?entry=/2014/09/forest_service_says_media_need.html" target="_blank">Print</a>
	</div>
	
	




	
		<a href="http://connect.oregonlive.com/user/rob-davis/index.html">
			
			   <span class="resimg Avatar" data-image="http://media.oregonlive.com/avatars/11255576.png" data-position="byline-avatar">Rob Davis | rdavis@oregonian.com</span>
			
		</a>
	



	



By

	
		
	
		
			<span class="author vcard"><a class="bl" href="http://connect.oregonlive.com/user/rob-davis/posts.html">
	
		
	
	
	
	
	Rob Davis | rdavis@oregonian.com
</a></span>
		
	
<span style="display:none; visibility:hidden;">The Oregonian</span>
		<br /> <a id="email_author" onclick="emailAuthor()">Email the author</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/robwdavis" target="_blank">Follow on Twitter</a>
	




	<br/>on September 23, 2014 at  5:46 PM, updated <span class="updated" title="2014-09-24T02:08:38Z">September 23, 2014 at  7:08 PM</span>
	<div id="sponsor_tablet">  
		<div class="sub-sponsor"></div>
	</div>
</div><!-- /Byline -->

                  <div id="social_top">
</div><!-- /social_top -->

